parameters: Phew... Oh, welcome! Are you staying the night?

...No. This inn seems to have fewer guests compared to
others, doesn't it?

Ahaha. You're quite direct, aren't you? I like that. I'm
getting on in years, you see. I've been thinking of handing
over this old inn to someone and retiring...
Eh? You're going to sell this inn?

That's right. As you can see, I left the roof leaking and
the decay has progressed. I wonder if there's someone who
would buy it? If I could sell it for about 50,000 mon, I
could retire comfortably.
Understood. I will buy this inn!

Yes. I have the money right here. Please, let me take over
this inn.

Oh, that's wonderful! Alright then. From today on, this inn
is yours. Use it as you like.
Thank you so much! I will take good care of it.

Well, as it stands, it's honestly too run-down for guests to
want to stay... I need to repair the leaks, replace the
tatami mats, and fix everything that's broken.

--Karin brought her carpentry tools and began fixing the
inn!

Phew... Well, that should do it. It's not new, but it's much
cleaner now.

...Oh my? If you look at the state of it now, it's amazing,
isn't it? Did you fix everything by yourself? It's become
quite splendid compared to before.

This is rice and pickles made from vegetables from my field.
If you're going to run an inn, you'll need to prepare dinner
too. There's plenty, so feel free to use it.
Wow, I'm so happy! I'll use it without hesitation\I[15]

(Too bad, I don't have the money right now. Maybe some other
time...)
I'm sorry. I can't make a decision right this moment...
No rush. Come back again sometime.

I'm sorry to have kept you waiting... I will definitely
repay you as soon as I can arrange the money...

(This inn... it's so old... It seems they're busy, so I
won't speak to them for now.)

Hey, Madam Innkeeper. The bill for the miso from the month
before last still hasn't been paid, you know? There's a
limit to how much I can put on the tab, so please settle it
soon.
